 124 class Py_buffer(Structure):
 125     _fields_ = [
 126         ("buf", c_void_p),
 127         ("obj", py_object),
 128         ("len", c_ssize_t),
 129         ("itemsize", c_ssize_t),

 135         ("suboffsets", c_ssize_p),
 136         ("internal", c_void_p),

 139     if PY2:
 140         _fields_.insert(-1, ("smalltable", c_ssize_t * 2))

 148 # On PyPy we cannot get buffers so our ability to operate here is
 149 # serverly limited.
 150 if pythonapi is None:
 151     get_buffer = None
 152 else:
 153 
 154     def get_buffer(obj, writable=False):
 155         buf = Py_buffer()
 156         flags = PyBUF_WRITABLE if writable else PyBUF_SIMPLE
 157         PyObject_GetBuffer(py_object(obj), byref(buf), flags)
 158         try:
 159             buffer_type = c_char * buf.len
 160             return buffer_type.from_address(buf.buf)
 161         finally:
 162             PyBuffer_Release(byref(buf))

 165 def get_long_path(short_path):
 166     # type: (Text, str) -> Text
 167     BUFFER_SIZE = 500
 168     buffer = create_unicode_buffer(BUFFER_SIZE)
 169     get_long_path_name = windll.kernel32.GetLongPathNameW
 170     get_long_path_name(to_text(short_path), buffer, BUFFER_SIZE)
 171     return buffer.value

 174 class _WindowsConsoleRawIOBase(io.RawIOBase):
 175     def __init__(self, handle):
 176         self.handle = handle
 177 
 178     def isatty(self):
 179         io.RawIOBase.isatty(self)
 180         return True
 181 
 182 
 183 class _WindowsConsoleReader(_WindowsConsoleRawIOBase):
 184     def readable(self):
 185         return True
 186 
 187     def readinto(self, b):
 188         bytes_to_be_read = len(b)
 189         if not bytes_to_be_read:
 190             return 0
 191         elif bytes_to_be_read % 2:
 192             raise ValueError(
 193                 "cannot read odd number of bytes from " "UTF-16-LE encoded console"
 194             )
 195 
 196         buffer = get_buffer(b, writable=True)
 197         code_units_to_be_read = bytes_to_be_read // 2
 198         code_units_read = c_ulong()
 199 
 200         rv = ReadConsoleW(
 201             self.handle, buffer, code_units_to_be_read, byref(code_units_read), None
 202         )
 203         if GetLastError() == ERROR_OPERATION_ABORTED:
 204             # wait for KeyboardInterrupt
 205             time.sleep(0.1)
 206         if not rv:
 207             raise OSError("Windows error: %s" % GetLastError())
 208 
 209         if buffer[0] == EOF:
 210             return 0
 211         return 2 * code_units_read.value
 212 
 213 
 214 class _WindowsConsoleWriter(_WindowsConsoleRawIOBase):
 215     def writable(self):
 216         return True
 217 
 218     @staticmethod
 219     def _get_error_message(errno):
 220         if errno == ERROR_SUCCESS:
 221             return "ERROR_SUCCESS"
 222         elif errno == ERROR_NOT_ENOUGH_MEMORY:
 223             return "ERROR_NOT_ENOUGH_MEMORY"
 224         return "Windows error %s" % errno
 225 
 226     def write(self, b):
 227         bytes_to_be_written = len(b)
 228         buf = get_buffer(b)
 229         code_units_to_be_written = min(bytes_to_be_written, MAX_BYTES_WRITTEN) // 2
 230         code_units_written = c_ulong()
 231 
 232         WriteConsoleW(
 233             self.handle, buf, code_units_to_be_written, byref(code_units_written), None
 234         )
 235         bytes_written = 2 * code_units_written.value
 236 
 237         if bytes_written == 0 and bytes_to_be_written > 0:
 238             raise OSError(self._get_error_message(GetLastError()))
 239         return bytes_written

 242 class ConsoleStream(object):
 243     def __init__(self, text_stream, byte_stream):
 244         self._text_stream = text_stream
 245         self.buffer = byte_stream
 246 
 247     @property
 248     def name(self):
 249         return self.buffer.name
 250 
 251     @property
 252     def fileno(self):
 253         return self.buffer.fileno
 254 
 255     def write(self, x):
 256         if isinstance(x, text_type):
 257             return self._text_stream.write(x)
 258         try:
 259             self.flush()
 260         except Exception:
 261             pass
 262         return self.buffer.write(x)
 263 
 264     def writelines(self, lines):
 265         for line in lines:
 266             self.write(line)
 267 
 268     def __getattr__(self, name):
 269         try:
 270             return getattr(self._text_stream, name)
 271         except io.UnsupportedOperation:
 272             return getattr(self.buffer, name)
 273 
 274     def isatty(self):
 275         return self.buffer.isatty()
 276 
 277     def __repr__(self):
 278         return "<ConsoleStream name=%r encoding=%r>" % (self.name, self.encoding)

 281 class WindowsChunkedWriter(object):
 282     """
 283     Wraps a stream (such as stdout), acting as a transparent proxy for all
 284     attribute access apart from method 'write()' which we wrap to write in
 285     limited chunks due to a Windows limitation on binary console streams.
 286     """
 287 
 288     def __init__(self, wrapped):
 289         # double-underscore everything to prevent clashes with names of
 290         # attributes on the wrapped stream object.
 291         self.__wrapped = wrapped
 292 
 293     def __getattr__(self, name):
 294         return getattr(self.__wrapped, name)
 295 
 296     def write(self, text):
 297         total_to_write = len(text)
 298         written = 0
 299 
 300         while written < total_to_write:
 301             to_write = min(total_to_write - written, MAX_BYTES_WRITTEN)
 302             self.__wrapped.write(text[written : written + to_write])
 303             written += to_write
 304

 306 _wrapped_std_streams = set()

 309 def _wrap_std_stream(name):
 310     # Python 2 & Windows 7 and below
 311     if PY2 and sys.getwindowsversion()[:2] <= (6, 1) and name not in _wrapped_std_streams:
 312         setattr(sys, name, WindowsChunkedWriter(getattr(sys, name)))
 313         _wrapped_std_streams.add(name)

 319         "utf-16-le",

 321         line_buffering=True,

 323     return ConsoleStream(text_stream, buffer_stream)

 346 if PY2:
 347 
 348     def _hash_py_argv():
 349         return zlib.crc32("\x00".join(sys.argv[1:]))
 350 
 351     _initial_argv_hash = _hash_py_argv()
 352 
 353     def _get_windows_argv():
 354         argc = c_int(0)
 355         argv_unicode = CommandLineToArgvW(GetCommandLineW(), byref(argc))
 356         try:
 357             argv = [argv_unicode[i] for i in range(0, argc.value)]
 358         finally:
 359             LocalFree(argv_unicode)
 360             del argv_unicode
 361 
 362         if not hasattr(sys, "frozen"):
 363             argv = argv[1:]
 364             while len(argv) > 0:
 365                 arg = argv[0]
 366                 if not arg.startswith("-") or arg == "-":
 367                     break
 368                 argv = argv[1:]
 369                 if arg.startswith(("-c", "-m")):
 370                     break
 371 
 372         return argv[1:]

 375 _stream_factories = {0: _get_text_stdin, 1: _get_text_stdout, 2: _get_text_stderr}

 378 def _get_windows_console_stream(f, encoding, errors):
 379     if (
 380         get_buffer is not None
 381         and encoding in ("utf-16-le", None)
 382         and errors in ("strict", None)
 383         and hasattr(f, "isatty")
 384         and f.isatty()
 385     ):
 386         if isinstance(f, ConsoleStream):
 387             return f
 388         func = _stream_factories.get(f.fileno())
 389         if func is not None:
 390             if not PY2:
 391                 f = getattr(f, "buffer", None)
 392                 if f is None:
 393                     return None
 394             else:
 395                 # If we are on Python 2 we need to set the stream that we
 396                 # deal with to binary mode as otherwise the exercise if a
 397                 # bit moot.  The same problems apply as for
 398                 # get_binary_stdin and friends from _compat.
 399                 msvcrt.setmode(f.fileno(), os.O_BINARY)
 400             return func(f)

 403 def hide_cursor():
 404     cursor_info = CONSOLE_CURSOR_INFO()

 421 def _walk_for_powershell(directory):
 422     for path, dirs, files in os.walk(directory):
 423         powershell = next(
 424             iter(fn for fn in files if fn.lower() == "powershell.exe"), None
 425         )
 426         if powershell is not None:
 427             return os.path.join(directory, powershell)
 428         for subdir in dirs:
 429             powershell = _walk_for_powershell(os.path.join(directory, subdir))
 430             if powershell:
 431                 return powershell
 432     return None
 433 
 434 
 435 def _get_powershell_path():
 436     paths = [
 437         os.path.expandvars(r"%windir%\{0}\WindowsPowerShell").format(subdir)
 438         for subdir in ("SysWOW64", "system32")
 439     ]
 440     powershell_path = next(iter(_walk_for_powershell(pth) for pth in paths), None)
 441     if not powershell_path:
 442         powershell_path, _ = run(
 443             ["where", "powershell"], block=True, nospin=True, return_object=False
 444         )
 445     if powershell_path:
 446         return powershell_path.strip()
 447     return None
 448 
 449 
 450 def _get_sid_with_powershell():
 451     powershell_path = _get_powershell_path()
 452     if not powershell_path:
 453         return None
 454     args = [
 455         powershell_path,
 456         "-ExecutionPolicy",
 457         "Bypass",
 458         "-Command",
 459         "Invoke-Expression '[System.Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity]::GetCurrent().user | Write-Host'",
 460     ]
 461     sid, _ = run(args, nospin=True)
 462     return sid.strip()

 465 def _get_sid_from_registry():
 466     try:
 467         import winreg
 468     except ImportError:
 469         import _winreg as winreg
 470     var_names = ("%USERPROFILE%", "%HOME%")
 471     current_user_home = next(iter(os.path.expandvars(v) for v in var_names if v), None)
 472     root, subkey = (
 473         winreg.HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE,
 474         r"Software\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\ProfileList",
 475     )
 476     subkey_names = []
 477     value = None
 478     matching_key = None
 479     try:
 480         with winreg.OpenKeyEx(root, subkey, 0, winreg.KEY_READ) as key:
 481             for i in count():
 482                 key_name = winreg.EnumKey(key, i)
 483                 subkey_names.append(key_name)
 484                 value = query_registry_value(
 485                     root, r"{0}\{1}".format(subkey, key_name), "ProfileImagePath"
 486                 )
 487                 if value and value.lower() == current_user_home.lower():
 488                     matching_key = key_name
 489                     break
 490     except OSError:
 491         pass
 492     if matching_key is not None:
 493         return matching_key
 494

 496 def get_value_from_tuple(value, value_type):
 497     try:
 498         import winreg
 499     except ImportError:
 500         import _winreg as winreg
 501     if value_type in (winreg.REG_SZ, winreg.REG_EXPAND_SZ):
 502         if "\0" in value:
 503             return value[: value.index("\0")]
 504         return value
 505     return None
 506 
 507 
 508 def query_registry_value(root, key_name, value):
 509     try:
 510         import winreg
 511     except ImportError:
 512         import _winreg as winreg
 513     try:
 514         with winreg.OpenKeyEx(root, key_name, 0, winreg.KEY_READ) as key:
 515             return get_value_from_tuple(*winreg.QueryValueEx(key, value))
 516     except OSError:
 517         return None
 518 
 519 
 520 def get_current_user():
 521     fns = (_get_sid_from_registry, _get_sid_with_powershell)
 522     for fn in fns:
 523         result = fn()
 524         if result:
 525             return result
 526     return None
